body:
Iron Man 3 Issue

Okay so this scene pisses me off so badly.

In Iron Man 3, when Tony starts experiencing legitimate anxiety issues. No one seems to get it.

At first, in the restaurant with Rhodey, he got triggered by the kid asking him about the worm hole.

He got into the Iron Man suit to keep himself safe.

Instead of anyone worrying about him, they gawk and stare, or better yet, record it.

And Rhodey doesn’t even really help him? Instead he tells him it doesn’t look good. Not good for Tony’s image.


So Tony runs away.


And then at night, when he has that panic attack/nightmare in his sleep. He accidentally calls the mark 42 suit, which grabs Pepper. The moment he wakes up he shuts it down, and takes a crow bar to it.

Tony was crying, shaking, freaking out, and I can understand Pepper was freaked.

My issue is that she left him there. She walked away from him, and told him to sleep alone.


Can you imagine how heartbreaking it probably was for Tony? To have the two people he needed the most not be there for him. To have no one there when he couldn’t sleep. When his anxiety ruled his entire life.


Tony deserved so much better in the Iron Man 3 movie and I will fight anyone on this.

summary: How about IronStrange in the HP universe for the AU ask game?
question: How about IronStrange in the HP universe for the AU ask game?
answer:
1. Tony and Stephen are both in Slytherin and they are the biggest rivals you will ever find, fight me on it. They are constantly at each other’s throats, trying to outdo one another, annoying their housemates so hard that they are kicked out of their common room on a regular base by their peers. (Despite being headboy—Stephen—and prefect—Tony.)

2. Secretly they enjoy their rivalry, because—honestly—they never found anyone to match their wit. Of course they have their respective friends, but they are just no match (except for Bruce, but he is too clever to participate in their cock measurement contest).

3. They both have a soft spot for first-year Hufflepuff Peter Parker, so nobody even dares to lay a hand on the tiny sunshine, who seems to have wrapped two of the most popular boys around his little finger. (‘If you touch him, Ross, I will jinx you into next century, I swear!’) It’s not uncommon to find both of them scowling at each other, while Peter shows them some magical creature he has found, completely oblivious to the tense air around his two big friends.

4. When their N.E.W.T.s are approaching, both of them are a little stressed, like everyone else. So it’s not uncommon to see them learning in the library, surrounded by books. However, nobody will believe the third-year Gryffindor who tells everyone that he saw Stephen Strange getting a book for Tony Stark from one of the higher shelves that Tony couldn’t reach himself. Nobody believes the same Gryffindor who tells them a week later, that he saw the both of them learning together in a secluded area of the library.

5. Fact is, Tony and Stephen can barely believe it themselves, but here they are, sitting together, learning together, helping each other. (Stealing glances when they think the other isn’t looking.) And if this learning session ends with a heated snog in one of the alcoves on the way to the Slytherin common room, well, nobody has to know.



Edit: I am an idiot. A read Hogwarts into your ask. Oops. Well, I think, this still counts?
